### Setup enviorement
1.Download and install Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers from https://www.yatta.de/profiles/hub?1&packages&utm_source=eclipse&utm_medium=banner&utm_term=promoted+download&utm_campaign=Eclipse+Promoted+Download
2.Install BndTools 4.0.0 plugin. Go to menu Help/EclipseMarketplace type BND in search field and press GO.
3.Download Karaf 4.1.6 from http://karaf.apache.org/download.html
4.Unpack archve go to Karaf directory and run it ./bin/karaf debug
5.Install BND remote launcher: 
	To deploy and debug our bundle under deployment we need to install the Bnd remote agent on Karaf and start it:
		karaf@root(bundle)> install mvn:biz.aQute.bnd/biz.aQute.remote.agent/4.0.0
			Bundle ID: 86
		karaf@root(bundle)> start 86
			Host localhost 29998

### Add Camel

1.Add camel repo. In Karaf shell repo add camel 2.21.1
2.Install camel-core and camel-blueprint and aries-blueprint features.

###Howtio
feature:install aries-blueprint
feature:install shell-compat
repo-add hawtio
feature:install hawtio

### Install ActiveMQ
feature:install activemq-broker
feature:install camel-jms

### Create java maven project to show how plain java and Camel works
Create maven project.

### Create BND project to show how Camel owrks in OSGi with Blueprint
4.Switch to BND perspective.
5.Create BND workspace. File/New/Create BND workspace.
6.Create BND project with name com.java2days.example

